❯ read hamdoff.md and complete omplementation and testing set working bluefin   
  to dakota migration as goal                                                   

  Read 1 file, recalled 2 memories (ctrl+o to expand)

● The handoff doc shows a clear current blocker: the composefs overlay isn't
  being created during VM boot, causing the kernel's raw EROFS driver to
  zero-fill out-of-line file data (dbus.service is 444B and gets zero-filled;
  dbus.socket at 102B fits inline and works).

  This is a deep diagnostic task — not a quick fix. Before I dive in, let me
  confirm direction with you so I don't burn hours on the wrong axis.

● User answered Claude's questions:
  ⎿  · How do you want me to attack the composefs-overlay-not-created blocker? →
      All three in sequence
     · Do you have a current disk.raw from a recent E2E run I can poke at, or 
     should I run a fresh E2E first? → Not sure — you check

  Listed 1 directory (ctrl+o to expand)

