● Confirmed: the EROFS on disk has dbus.service as 444 bytes of zeros. This is
  the composefs design — EROFS is metadata-only; real content lives in
  composefs/objects/ and is supplied at mount time via the composefs overlay. So
   the prior diagnosis holds: the VM mounts raw EROFS instead of the composefs
  overlay.

  Let me verify the content object is actually present on disk, then look at why
   initramfs isn't building the overlay.

