● Both dbus.service AND dbus.socket are zero-filled on raw EROFS — the HANDOFF's
   "inline threshold" theory is wrong. The real story is simpler: composefs is a
   content-addressed overlay, EROFS is metadata-only by design. If the overlay
  isn't built, every non-trivial file (passwd, polkitd, dbus.service, etc.)
  reads as zeros. That explains the polkitd exit 217 (user lookup fails —
  /etc/passwd is also zero-filled).

  Let me check whether the VM is actually booting the composefs entry or falling
   back, and what initramfs setup looks like.

