● Root cause identified. The dbus.service failure isn't an EROFS/composefs issue
   — it's a stale enablement symlink. Bluefin's /etc/systemd/system/dbus.service
   is a symlink to /usr/lib/systemd/system/dbus-broker.service. Dakota doesn't
  ship dbus-broker (it uses classic dbus), so after the /etc bind-mount, that
  symlink dangles. The cascade (polkit, NetworkManager, sshd) all flow from dbus
   being broken.

  The composefs overlay is working correctly. The migration's 3-way /etc merge
  is bringing forward symlinks that point to units only the source image had.

