      42 +### How the real bug was confirmed (this session)              
      43 +- Loopback-mounted `disk.raw` post-migration → EROFS at `compos
         +efs/images/<verity>` has dbus.service zero-filled (444B). This 
         +is **expected**: the EROFS holds only metadata; `trusted.overla
         +y.metacopy` + `trusted.overlay.redirect` xattrs point to conten
         +t objects in `composefs/objects/`.                             
      44 +- Confirmed fs-verity is enabled on btrfs filesystem (`compat_r
         +o_flags = VERITY`), enabled on the EROFS image and on content o
         +bjects (lsattr shows `V` flag).                                
      45 +- Mounted the composefs overlay on the host with `bootc interna
         +ls cfs --repo /var/mnt/diskraw/composefs mount <verity> /tmp/cf
         +s-mount` — `composefs:<hash>` overlay mounted successfully; `he
         +ad dbus.service` shows real content. So composefs works on this
         + kernel.                                                       
      46 +- qemu.log shows `initramfs-setup` exited 0 successfully, and E
         +ROFS mount line corresponds to the composefs internal lowerdir 
         +mount.                                                         
      47 +- The failing units are exactly those whose enablement symlinks
         + point to Dakota-absent /usr targets:                          
      48 +  - `/etc/systemd/system/dbus.service -> /usr/lib/systemd/syste
         +m/dbus-broker.service` (Dakota lacks dbus-broker)              
      49 +  - `/etc/systemd/system/multi-user.target.wants/{chronyd,sssd,
         +smartd,thermald,tuned,lm_sensors,nfs-client,…}.service` (simila
         +r)                                                             
      50 +- Each dangling symlink yields `Failed to load configuration: N
         +o such file or directory`; the dbus one cascades through polkit
         + → logind → sshd, killing post-reboot SSH.                     
      51  
      45 -### Cascade failure                                            
      46 -- `dbus.service` missing → polkit, logind, gdm, NetworkManager,
         - avahi, etc. all DEPEND-fail                                   
      47 -- `sshd.service` starts but can't authenticate without logind  
      48 -- E2E times out waiting for post-reboot SSH                    
      49 -                                                               
      50 -### Hypotheses for why composefs overlay fails                 
      51 -                                                               
      52 -1. **Composefs user-space library missing from initramfs.** The
         - initramfs is extracted from the Dakota OCI via skopeo streamin
         -g. If `libcomposefs.so.1` isn't included or is corrupted in the
         - extracted `initramfs.img`, the initramfs-setup falls back to r
         -aw EROFS.                                                      
      53 -2. **State directory layout mismatch.** The migration creates `
         -/sysroot/state/deploy/<verity>/` with etc, var, and imginfo. If
         - the initramfs expects a different directory layout (e.g. bootc
         -'s standard `/sysroot/state/` structure), it might fail to crea
         -te the overlay.                                                
      54 -3. **EROFS image structural issue.** The EROFS created by `boot
         -c internals cfs create-image` might be missing metadata that co
         -mposefs user-space needs. The `oci-config-<verity>` stream is c
         -onfirmed missing from the object store, suggesting the seal or 
         -create-image is incomplete.                                    
      55 -                                                               
