● Monitor(E2E progress: phase markers, BLS entries, post-reboot SSH, pass/fail)
  ⎿  Monitor started · task br7cso2i9 · timeout 3600s

● E2E launched. While it runs, I'll summarize what landed so far.

  Findings
  - The HANDOFF's "raw EROFS zero-fills out-of-line data" diagnosis was wrong.
  EROFS being metadata-only is by design — the composefs overlay supplies
  content via overlay.metacopy + overlay.redirect xattrs into
  composefs/objects/.
  - Verified the overlay works on the same kernel (7.0.7) on the host: bootc 
  internals cfs mount returned a composefs:<hash> overlay and dbus.service read
  back its real 444 bytes.
  - Real root cause: the 3-way /etc merge brings forward Bluefin's enablement
  symlinks. 102 of those symlinks point under /usr/* to files Dakota doesn't
  ship. The critical one is /etc/systemd/system/dbus.service → 
  /usr/lib/systemd/system/dbus-broker.service (Dakota uses classic dbus). That
  dangling symlink → systemd "Failed to load configuration: No such file or
  directory" → polkit/logind/sshd cascade-fail → E2E SSH timeout.

  Changes
  - src/mergetc.rs: added prune_dangling_usr_symlinks(etc_dir, target_root) + 2
  unit tests (57/57 pass).
  - src/migration/mod.rs: perform_etc_merge calls the prune after
  merge_etc_files, using the mounted target image as the resolution root.
  - HANDOFF.md: retracted the old root cause, added the new finding, updated
  next steps.

  In flight
  - E2E running in background; I'll report back on completion or at the 30-min
  fallback wakeup.

