● The disk.raw shows yesterday's state because qemu's writeback cache wasn't
  flushed (no cache=writethrough). But the inside-VM behavior reflects today's
  migration. The deeper bug — /etc/passwd merge drops system users — was present
   yesterday and still is.

  Both Bluefin and Dakota ship /usr/etc/passwd (factory) ~equal to live
  /etc/passwd on a freshly installed system. The 3-way merge does if old==cur, 
  take new → Dakota's minimal passwd → ~3 users → dbus/polkit/systemd-resolve
  all fail with 217/USER.

  Same trap for shadow/group/gshadow/subuid/subgid/machine-id. Fix: keep current
   unconditionally for these files.
