● The 217/USER is concretely "Unknown user 'messagebus'" — NSS lookup fails.
  Bluefin's /etc/passwd evidently doesn't have messagebus because Bluefin uses
  dbus-broker which doesn't need that user. My "always keep current" preserved
  that absence; Dakota's factory /etc/passwd has messagebus but I dropped it.
  Need a line-level merge: keep all current entries, then add any entries from
  new whose username isn't in current.

