● Real root cause found. The migration's mount_image for Phase 4's /etc merge
  falls back to raw EROFS (bootc cfs mount fails — oci-config-<verity> stream
  missing). Dakota's /etc/passwd reads as zeros, so my line-union merge sees no
  Dakota users to add.

  This is also what 81c7781 worked around for Phase 5 (boot artifacts) using
  skopeo streaming. Phase 4's etc-merge needs the same treatment, or we need to
  populate the missing stream. Let me look at Phase 5's skopeo approach and the
  migration code structure.

