● Found it — mergetc drops files that exist unchanged in source factory + live
  /etc when the target image doesn't have them. That's correct OSTree-style
  upgrade logic, but wrong for cross-image migration. For e2e-sshd.socket (baked
   into Bluefin's image, not in Dakota), this means the unit file gets dropped
  while the enablement symlink remains, breaking SSH.

