  Starting state: composefs entry was selected from systemd-boot but post-reboot
   SSH timed out — HANDOFF blamed raw-EROFS zero-fill of out-of-line data.

  What was actually wrong (each fixed this session):
  1. HANDOFF's diagnosis was wrong. EROFS being metadata-only is by design —
  composefs supplies content via overlay metacopy + redirect xattrs into
  composefs/objects/. Confirmed the overlay works on the same host kernel via
  bootc internals cfs mount. The cascade failures had a completely different
  root cause.
  2. Dangling /etc symlinks from the 3-way merge — 102 of them (e.g.
  dbus.service → /usr/lib/systemd/system/dbus-broker.service; Dakota uses
  classic dbus). Added prune_dangling_usr_symlinks to mergetc; Phase 4 walks
  merged /etc and drops /usr/* symlinks whose target doesn't exist in the target
   image.
  3. Identity-DB merge dropped system users. mount_image falls back to raw EROFS
   when the oci-config-<verity> stream is missing, and raw-EROFS zero-fills any
  file past the inline threshold. So /etc/passwd from the EROFS mount was all
  zeros → standard 3-way merge dropped Dakota's messagebus/polkitd/etc → dbus
  217/USER. Added extract_subtree_via_registry (skopeo-style layer streaming,
  oldest→newest, file-by-file) and use it as the merge source instead of the
  broken EROFS mount.
  4. Cross-image migration dropped source-only files (e2e-sshd.socket,
  flatpak-nuke-fedora.service). Standard OSTree upgrade rule "old==cur, new=None
   → drop" is wrong for cross-image migration. Changed to always preserve cur in
   that arm; renamed/flipped the corresponding test and added one guarding
  e2e-sshd.

  Resulting state: composefs boots, dbus/polkit/logind/sshd.service all start
  cleanly. New blocker (Task #9 + HANDOFF.md): per-connection sshd-session
  spawned via e2e-sshd.socket exits 255/EXCEPTION after 65ms with stderr going
  to journal (not console). Likely PAM/NSS plugin discrepancy between Bluefin's
  authselect config and what Dakota ships. Test suite: 60/60 passing.

✻ Brewed for 5m 34s

✻ Claude resuming /loop wakeup (Jun 15 6:15am)

❯ /loop continue: check E2E status and HANDOFF.md                               

